# accumulation-zorch Python byte-match dependencies.
#
# Pulled from the Fractalyze package index alongside upstream PyPI:
#   pip install -r requirements.in \
#     --extra-index-url https://fractalyze.github.io/pypi/simple/
#
# zorch itself arrives as a Bazel module (see MODULE.bazel), not a pip dep.
#
# LOCKSTEP with the zorch git_override pin in MODULE.bazel: accumulation-zorch's
# py_tests depend on BOTH this repo's pip hub and zorch's, so both must resolve
# frx to the identical wheel — otherwise the runfiles carry two frx builds and
# the arkworks byte-match silently skews. zorch @ 33f2837 pins this exact set;
# bump both together. The frx Pasta build (0.10 line) registers the Pasta curve
# dtypes; zk-dtypes 0.0.10 carries them, and frx requires that floor anyway.
# CPU wheels only — the GPU byte-match is on the Rust side.
#
# This floor is load-bearing beyond the usual "stay current": it carries frx's
# FRX_* -> JAX_* env alias (2026-07-16), which the FRX_PLATFORMS spellings in
# .bazelrc / bench.sh / README depend on. The dev20260715051143 line this
# replaced predates the alias and ignores those names outright, so the backend
# would fall back to the default instead of the pinned CPU — green on a
# CPU-only box, quietly on CUDA elsewhere. Do not drop below a 2026-07-16
# build without respelling those vars JAX_*.
absl-py
numpy
frx==0.10.0.dev20260716113241
frxlib==0.10.0.dev20260716113241
zk-dtypes==0.0.10
